request.description:
Create auth session context after Firebase token verification. Returns profile if the user already exists, or indicates the user must complete onboarding.

Request Body:
- Optional: roleType ('CUSTOMER' or 'BARBER'), deprecated and ignored by backend.

Response (New User):
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "New user. Please complete your profile.",
  "data": {
    "isNewUser": true,
    "firebaseUid": "abc123",
    "phoneNumber": "+1234567890",
    "email": "barber@example.com"
  }
}

Response (Existing Barber User):
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Login successful",
  "data": {
    "isNewUser": false,
    "user": {...},
    "profile": {
      "shopName": "Downtown Cuts",
      "shopOwner": "John Doe",
      "businessCategory": "Barber",
      "shopLocation": "MG Road, Bengaluru",
      "amenities": [...],
      "workingDays": [...],
      "workingHours": {
        "opensAt": "09:00",
        "closesAt": "20:00"
      },
      "breakTimings": [...],
      "shopImages": ["https://..."]
    }
  }
}

Deleted/disabled accounts:
- Return `401 Unauthorized`
- Cannot create a new session or re-onboard with the same deleted account token
